1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,300
This is Runwiser.

2
00:00:03,420 --> 00:00:06,720
It turns repeated agent work into reusable workflow assets, with proof attached.

3
00:00:06,720 --> 00:00:11,860
The landing page leads with the operating model.

4
00:00:11,980 --> 00:00:17,120
Runs create evidence, gates check quality, and only verified work moves forward.

5
00:00:17,120 --> 00:00:21,220
This is not loose multi-agent parallelism.

6
00:00:21,340 --> 00:00:25,440
Specialized roles hand work across bounded review and verification steps.

7
00:00:25,440 --> 00:00:29,860
The wiki also shows up on the landing page as a public knowledge surface.

8
00:00:29,980 --> 00:00:34,400
That makes the system feel browsable instead of hidden.

9
00:00:34,400 --> 00:00:39,060
Then the live wiki service makes that idea concrete.

10
00:00:39,180 --> 00:00:43,840
You can open the catalog, enter a page, and browse promoted workflow knowledge directly.

11
00:00:43,840 --> 00:00:48,500
The repository mirrors the same lifecycle.

12
00:00:48,620 --> 00:00:53,280
Architecture documents explain the layers, the boundaries, and where each asset belongs.

13
00:00:53,280 --> 00:00:59,380
The proof is not abstract.

14
00:00:59,500 --> 00:01:05,600
You can see runs, workflows, scripts, knowledge assets, and scenario wrappers living in separate layers inside the repo.

15
00:01:05,600 --> 00:01:10,260
That is the point of Runwiser.

16
00:01:10,380 --> 00:01:15,040
Make agent work measurable, improvable, and reusable by preserving evidence before promotion.

